wiki.text:
'Equalizer' or 'equaliser' (see spelling differences) may refer to:

;Science and technology *Equalization, the process of adjusting the strength of
certain frequencies within a signal *Equalization (audio), frequency-dependent
processing of audio signals *An Equalizer (communications) used in
telecommunications *Equalizer (mathematics), the solution set of an equation *A
term sometimes used to describe a whippletree

;Entertainment *[[The Equalizer]], an American action-adventure television
series ** ''The Equalizer'' (film), film based on the TV show *stagename for
Bill Dannenhauer

;Videogaming *A weapon in the video game [[Team Fortress 2]] that deals more
damage as the player loses health. *Equalizer (Datel), a game-hacking cheat
cartridge by Datel

;Music *"Equalizer" (k-os song), a song by hip hop artist k-os *NFL Films song
by Sam Spence

;Weaponry *GAU-12 Equalizer, a type of Gatling gun *A slang term for a gun **
Nickname for the Colt Single Action Army

;Other *Equaliser (sports), a goal or run that ties the game *Equalizer
(computer program), a program which helps Stephen Hawking to talk.

*Equal-i-zer, a brand of towing hitch *Equalizer (Auto Glass Tools),
www.equalizer.com.
